WEBVTT

00:00:04.459 --> 00:00:10.415
This message comes with care from the Central Autopsy Service at Henry Ford Hospital.

00:00:10.415 --> 00:00:16.795
If you’re watching this, someone you love has died — and we are so sorry.

00:00:16.795 --> 00:00:19.348
No words make this moment easier.

00:00:19.348 --> 00:00:25.303
In the next few minutes, we’ll walk with you through what happens next, gently

00:00:25.303 --> 00:00:29.982
and one step at a time — including questions about autopsy

00:00:29.982 --> 00:00:33.385
— and the ways we can support you.

00:00:33.385 --> 00:00:35.937
You don’t need to remember everything.

00:00:35.937 --> 00:00:38.915
We will help you along the way.

00:00:40.115 --> 00:00:44.169
In the hours after a death, you are not alone.

00:00:44.169 --> 00:00:47.007
A doctor confirms your loved one’s death.

00:00:47.007 --> 00:00:50.656
Our nurses care for your loved one with dignity.

00:00:50.656 --> 00:00:59.170
And if you wish, you may take time to sit together — to pray, to talk, or simply to be near.

00:00:59.170 --> 00:01:01.603
There is no need to hurry.

00:01:01.603 --> 00:01:06.873
If your faith or culture holds traditions for these hours, please tell us.

00:01:06.873 --> 00:01:10.522
We will do all we can to honor them.

00:01:10.522 --> 00:01:15.793
Depending on the circumstances, there may also be a question about an autopsy

00:01:15.793 --> 00:01:19.847
or the county medical examiner may need to be involved.

00:01:21.047 --> 00:01:24.225
An autopsy is a careful medical examination

00:01:24.225 --> 00:01:28.310
performed by a specially trained doctor called a pathologist.

00:01:28.310 --> 00:01:34.212
It can help answer questions about an illness, or about why someone died.

00:01:34.212 --> 00:01:39.205
Some families choose one, because answers can bring peace of mind

00:01:39.205 --> 00:01:42.837
— and what we learn can help others.

00:01:42.837 --> 00:01:48.738
Michigan law requires certain deaths to be reported to the county medical examiner

00:01:48.738 --> 00:01:55.094
— for example, after an accident, or when a death is sudden or unexpected.

00:01:55.094 --> 00:01:59.179
When that happens, Henry Ford contacts the medical examiner

00:01:59.179 --> 00:02:02.357
who decides whether an autopsy is required.

00:02:02.357 --> 00:02:05.988
If it is, we will let you know.

00:02:05.988 --> 00:02:13.252
And whatever the path, please hold on to this: your loved one is treated with care

00:02:13.252 --> 00:02:15.975
dignity and respect, at every step.

00:02:15.975 --> 00:02:18.699
We make room for your beliefs.

00:02:18.699 --> 00:02:26.416
In most cases, an autopsy does not delay funeral plans, and it does not prevent a viewing.

00:02:26.416 --> 00:02:29.594
Results take time — often several weeks.

00:02:29.594 --> 00:02:36.403
When they are ready, we will share them and answer your questions in plain language.

00:02:36.403 --> 00:02:42.304
At any moment, your care team can connect you with our Autopsy Service.

00:02:43.504 --> 00:02:49.546
In the days ahead, a few practical steps will ask for your attention.

00:02:49.546 --> 00:02:52.800
They do not all happen at once.

00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:55.124
First: choosing a funeral home.

00:02:55.124 --> 00:03:01.630
Once you have, tell our staff, and we will arrange your loved one’s transfer.

00:03:01.630 --> 00:03:04.884
The funeral home may ask for details

00:03:04.884 --> 00:03:10.461
— your loved one’s full name, date of birth, clothing, or photos.

00:03:10.461 --> 00:03:12.785
Bring someone you trust along.

00:03:12.785 --> 00:03:19.292
The funeral home will also help you order certified death certificates; many families need

00:03:19.292 --> 00:03:22.545
ten or more, for banks and insurance.

00:03:22.545 --> 00:03:28.587
Legal and financial matters can wait their turn — over weeks, not days.

00:03:28.587 --> 00:03:33.700
And our printed guide, After the Death of a Loved One

00:03:33.700 --> 00:03:37.418
holds all of it as a simple checklist.

00:03:37.418 --> 00:03:38.812
Keep it close.

00:03:38.812 --> 00:03:41.601
Use it when you are ready.

00:03:42.801 --> 00:03:45.873
Through all of this, there is grief.

00:03:45.873 --> 00:03:50.700
You may feel shock, sadness, anger, numbness, guilt — even relief.

00:03:50.700 --> 00:03:52.894
Sometimes all in one day.

00:03:52.894 --> 00:03:58.160
There is no right way to grieve, and no schedule for it.

00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:00.354
Please don’t carry it alone.

00:04:00.354 --> 00:04:03.425
Lean on the people who love you.

00:04:03.425 --> 00:04:08.691
Our chaplains are here for people of every faith, and of none

00:04:08.691 --> 00:04:12.202
— including Catholic sacramental care, if you wish.

00:04:12.202 --> 00:04:17.468
Henry Ford’s grief support groups are open to everyone in our community

00:04:17.468 --> 00:04:24.050
and SandCastles gives children and teens a safe place to grieve with others their age.

00:04:24.050 --> 00:04:31.949
If grief ever feels heavier than you can bear, call or text 9-8-8 — any hour, any day.

00:04:31.949 --> 00:04:38.531
From all of us at Henry Ford Health, we are so sorry for your loss.

00:04:38.531 --> 00:04:44.675
If you have questions about your loved one’s care, an autopsy, or finding support

00:04:44.675 --> 00:04:45.991
— please call.

00:04:45.991 --> 00:04:48.185
We are here for you.
